                                   <p>Depending on your Organization&rsquo;s privacy settings, you can invite guest users to collaborate on a workspace.&nbsp;Guests do not have to belong to any Organization in Bluescape prior to being invited. In addition, they can only see the workspaces they have been invited to &mdash; they cannot see any Public workspaces in the Organization.</p>
<br />
Guests will have the permissions of the corresponding workspace role set by the Admin. However, for security purposes, guests cannot perform the following tasks, regardless of their workspace role:

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li>Create new workspaces</li>
	<li>Invite other guests and collaborators to view a workspace</li>
	<li>View the list of users in the Organization</li>
</ul>
<br />
<b>Note</b>: For Organizations with Custom Roles enabled, guests can be assigned specific custom roles (while still maintaining the three restrictions above).<br />
