    <h2>
        Adding a Guest to a Workspace
    </h2>
    Guest users can be invited to a workspace by Users or Admins. Guests do not have to belong to any Organization in Bluescape prior to being invited. However, the role does have certain limitations.<br />
<br />
To add a guest to a workspace:
<p>&nbsp;</p>

<ol>
	<li>Follow the steps to add a collaborator to a workspace. If the collaborator does not already belong to the Organization, the system designates them as a guest. You will see the drop-down <b>Create &ldquo;&lt;guest email address&gt;&rdquo;</b> beneath the guest&rsquo;s email address in the <b>Add collaborator</b> pop-up window.&nbsp;</li>
    <li>An invitation is sent to the guest&#39;s email address.&nbsp;</li>
    <li>Guests that are new to Bluescape&nbsp;will be sent to the Bluescape account creation&nbsp;page. They must enter a name and password, and select their industry. Clicking <b>Accept invitation</b>&nbsp;completes the login process.</li>
    <li>The guest can now access the workspace they were invited to.</li>
</ol>
<br />
<b>Note</b>: Guest users will have a badge indicating their guest role on the <b>Workspace Collaborators</b> page.<br />
    <br />
    <h2>
        Setting Admin Approval for Guest Invites
    </h2>
    
    <p>Organizations may be configured to require that guests are approved by an Administrator before receiving a workspace invitation. The following steps detail the approval process:</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<ol>
	<li>A user invites the guest to a workspace.</li>
	<li>Admininstrator(s) receive&nbsp;a request for&nbsp;approval&nbsp;email.</li>
	<li>Administrator approves the invitation.</li>
	<li>Guest receives an invitation email.</li>
	<li>The guest can now enter the workspace.</li>
</ol>
<br />
To enable the guest approval process:
<p>&nbsp;</p>

<ol>
	<li>Login to Bluescape as an Administrator.&nbsp;</li>
	<li>Click the Org tree icon to open the&nbsp;<b>Organization Settings</b>&nbsp;page in the portal.</li>
	<li>Locate the <b>User invite settings</b> section. Toggle the <b>Guest invites require admin approva</b>l to the blue &quot;on&quot;&nbsp;position.</li>
</ol>

